data.name: comboBackupSize.ToolTip
data.value: [null] = Comment Size of the save file used by the ROM. Either memory in cartridge or Controller Pak memory. SRAM on Cart and SRAM Controller Pak is usually 32768 bytes. EEPROM is usually 512 bytes or 2048 bytes. Flash is usually 131072 bytes.

data.name: checkNeedPreParse.ToolTip
data.value: ▣ = Comment, ▢ = Disabled, ☑ = Enabled PreParse basically grabs Graphical info via Temporary Lists via RAM and loads the data before loading the Game from Textures to Geometry data etc. Kind of like a Cache stacks files up instead loading on the fly. This can sometimes fix games that crash some may require it.
